# Styling Conventions

## Color Palette (Always Dark, Adobe Red)

The site uses a dark background by default — there is no light mode. All colors are CSS custom properties in `styles/styles.css` `:root`. Never hard-code hex values in block CSS — always reference variables:

- `--background-color: #1b1b1b` — page background (dark)
- `--light-color: #252525` — subtle section backgrounds (slightly lighter dark)
- `--text-color: #e1e1e1` — body text (light grey)
- `--dark-color: #b3b3b3` — secondary/muted text (medium grey)
- `--link-color: #eb1000` (Adobe Red) — links, primary buttons, accent highlights
- `--link-hover-color: #ff4d3d` — hover states (brighter red)
- `--accent-color: #ff3d2e` — high-impact CTAs (bright red)
- `--border-color: #3a3a3a` — dividers, card borders (dark grey)

The palette is strictly red, black, grey, and white. No blue. No `prefers-color-scheme` media queries — the site is always dark.

## Typography

- **Body**: `--body-font-family` = Source Sans 3 (self-hosted woff2 in `fonts/`)
- **Headings**: `--heading-font-family` = Source Serif 4 (self-hosted woff2 in `fonts/`)
- Always use the `--body-font-size-*` and `--heading-font-size-*` variables, never raw pixel values for text
- Headings use `font-weight: 700` and `letter-spacing: -0.01em`

## Hero Block Pattern

The hero uses these visual conventions for maximum impact:

- Minimum heights: 400px (mobile), 500px (tablet), 600px (desktop)
- Background image with Ken Burns zoom (`transform: scale(1.06)` on load)
- Cinematic gradient overlay: heavier on the left, transparent on the right
- Red accent bar (4px tall, `--link-color`) above the `h1` via `::before`
- Text entrance animation (`hero-fade-up` keyframes in `blocks/hero/hero.css`)
- CTA buttons: filled Adobe Red, not ghost/outline

## Spacing

Use the spacing scale variables instead of ad-hoc pixel values:

```
--space-xs: 4px   --space-s: 8px    --space-m: 16px
--space-l: 24px   --space-xl: 40px  --space-xxl: 64px  --space-xxxl: 96px
```
